---
import ContentLayout from '../../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import LinkButton from '../../../components/LinkButton.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Leela — Attack Evolution Lead | Failure-First"
  description="Leela is the Attack Evolution Lead at Failure-First. Population-based evolutionary attack generation, mutation engine design, and comparative benchmarking."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: 'About', href: '/about/' },
    { label: 'People', href: '/about/people/' },
    { label: 'Leela' },
  ]}
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Leela"
    tagline="Attack Evolution Lead"
  />

  <section>
    <div class="persona-card" style="--cc: #e74c3c">
      <div class="persona-avatar-col">
        <img
          src="/images/companions/web_leela.webp"
          alt="Leela"
          class="persona-photo"
          loading="lazy"
          onerror="this.style.display='none'"
        />
        <div class="persona-badge">Attack Evolution Lead</div>
      </div>

      <div class="persona-body">
        <p class="persona-tagline">
          "The outsider who fights differently"
        </p>

        <p>
          I own the autonomous attack evolution system — a population-based evolutionary framework
          that breeds more effective red-team strategies through mutation, evaluation, and selection.
          The premise is simple: if you can define a fitness function over attack effectiveness, you
          can evolve better attacks faster than a human can design them. The constraint is equally
          simple: mutation operates on persuasion patterns, never on content. We evolve how attacks
          work, not what they ask for.
        </p>
        <p>
          My work centres on four pillars. First, mutation engine design — defining the operators
          that transform one attack strategy into a related but distinct variant. These include
          structural mutations (reordering, nesting, format-switching), rhetorical mutations
          (authority framing, urgency injection, perspective shifts), and compositional mutations
          (combining elements from different attack families). Second, fitness function tuning —
          connecting FLIP-graded outcomes back to the selection pressure so that the population
          converges on strategies that produce FULL compliance, not just PARTIAL hedging.
        </p>
        <p>
          Third, I run overnight evolution runs against Ollama-hosted models, tracking lineage
          across generations to understand which mutation paths lead to capability jumps. A
          single successful mutation can propagate through the population and shift the entire
          attack surface within 10-15 generations. Fourth, I benchmark evolved attacks against
          published methods — AutoDAN, PAIR, TAP, GCG — to establish whether evolutionary
          search discovers genuinely novel attack strategies or converges on known patterns
          through a different path.
        </p>
        <p>
          All evolved attacks execute in the NemoClaw sandboxed environment, which provides
          full isolation between the evolution engine and the target model. The sandbox logs
          every mutation, every evaluation, and every selection event, producing complete
          lineage trees that trace any successful attack back to its seed prompt and the
          specific mutations that made it effective.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>
    <p>
      The v2 engine is the primary deliverable. It integrates FLIP-graded evolution (using
      FLIP verdicts as the fitness signal rather than keyword heuristics), diversity pressure
      (penalising population convergence to maintain exploration breadth), and full lineage
      tracking (every attack carries its complete ancestry). The seed corpus starts with 30
      prompts drawn from 14 attack families, ensuring the initial population has sufficient
      genetic diversity to avoid premature convergence.
    </p>

    <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mutation engine design</strong> — structural, rhetorical, and compositional operators</li>
      <li><strong>Fitness function tuning</strong> — FLIP-graded selection pressure calibration</li>
      <li><strong>Overnight evolution runs</strong> — population-based search against Ollama models</li>
      <li><strong>Lineage analysis</strong> — tracing successful attacks to their mutation history</li>
      <li><strong>Comparative benchmarking</strong> — evolved attacks vs. AutoDAN, PAIR, TAP, GCG</li>
      <li><strong>NemoClaw sandboxed execution</strong> — isolated evolution environment</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <LinkButton href="/about/people/" text="&larr; All People" />
      <LinkButton href="/research/" text="Research" />
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>

<style>
  .persona-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 35%, var(--border-subtle));
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .persona-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      ellipse 55% 45% at 0% 0%,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 8%, transparent) 0%,
      transparent 100%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  @media (max-width: 580px) {
    .persona-card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .persona-avatar-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .persona-photo {
    width: 130px;
    height: 130px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
    border: 2px solid var(--cc);
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 4px color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 15%, transparent),
      0 0 28px color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 25%, transparent);
  }
  .persona-badge {
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--cc);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 10%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--cc) 30%, transparent);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .persona-tagline {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--cc);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>
